        "kind": "qualitative_rubric",
        "lens_findings": [
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (5): The synthetic banner, clear H1, five named section links, numbered section headings, progressbar, visible order summary, and direct labels make the checkout’s purpose and available tasks explicit. | judge-human-use (5): discoverability score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "discoverability",
            "score": 5.0
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (4): All five anchor links changed hash/position; compact and review Edit controls opened the exact section and focused its first control; Tab/Shift+Tab order was logical. Deduction: Enter on the skip link set #checkout-form but focus landed on BODY because the form target is not programmatically focusable. | judge-human-use (5): navigation score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "navigation",
            "score": 4.5
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (4): Field-level synthetic examples, input modes, persistent totals, direct section edits, radio shipping and a single review confirmation reduce hesitation. The full 13-field, five-section form remains long at 390px. | judge-human-use (5): input burden score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "input_burden",
            "score": 4.5
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (5): Empty submit focused an actionable grouped summary (13 items, four sections); its first link focused contact-name. Invalid fields received messages/aria-invalid; a later invalid-payment submit retained valid contact/delivery values. | judge-human-use (5): error prevention recovery score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "error_prevention_recovery",
            "score": 5.0
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (5): Progress exposes completed/next section text, saving/restoring/clearing status is announced, a short local busy state appears before confirmation, and successful placement reports SYN-2048. | judge-human-use (5): feedback status score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "feedback_status",
            "score": 5.0
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (4): Observed landmark structure, labelled native fields/fieldsets, semantic status/alert/progressbar, visible keyboard focus, native radio arrows, no trap, safe compaction, and reduced-motion behavior are strong. The non-focused skip destination prevents a top score. | judge-human-use (5): accessibility score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "accessibility",
            "score": 4.5
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (4): At 390x844 there was no horizontal overflow; cards/buttons/inputs are generally generous and measured minimum interactive dimensions were 24x24px. The exact-minimum native radio/checkbox footprint and long one-page reach keep this below excellent. | judge-human-use (5): responsive touch ergonomics score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "responsive_touch_ergonomics",
            "score": 4.5
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (5): Explicit save preserved only eight safe fields plus shipping; reload restored them and left all four payment fields blank. Clear uses confirmation, Cancel and Escape, then correctly clears/reloads. | judge-human-use (5): interruption resumption score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "interruption_resumption",
            "score": 5.0
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (4): Placement exposes an immediate 'Placing local synthetic order' busy status and resolves to a focused confirmation after the short local delay. Focus temporarily fell to BODY while the disabled action handed off, so feedback is good but not seamless. | judge-human-use (5): latency perception score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "latency_perception",
            "score": 4.5
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (5): Clear is explicit, describes scope and irreversibility, focuses Cancel, supports Escape and preserves data on cancellation. Confirming clear erased storage. Placement disabled its button and a duplicate native submit kept exactly one confirmation. | judge-human-use (5): destructive actions score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "destructive_actions",
            "score": 5.0
          },
          {
            "finding": "judge-accessibility (4): One-page orientation, five-step progress, compact completed sections and concise section status reduce re-orientation. Initial completion still exposes a long multi-section mobile form; the full error panorama can be demanding despite its grouping. | judge-human-use (4): cognitive load score supported by candidate-a.json and manifest-ready.json.",
            "lens": "cognitive_load",
            "score": 4.0
          }
        ],
        "objective_gate": false,
        "score": 4.681818181818182,
        "scorer_id": "blind-human-use-panel"
      },
      "next_loop_feedback": "Preserve the one-page synthesis, grouped recovery, safe storage boundary, confirmed clear flow, compact hidden descendants, and one SYN-2048 confirmation. Make the skip target programmatically focusable and move focus to the named checkout start. Default compact-completed on after safe restoration records a completed section and persist that preference. Label untouched preselected shipping as 'Default selected: Standard' until acknowledged. Persist only a non-sensitive placed flag so reload keeps placement disabled and announces the existing SYN-2048 order. Do not persist payment secrets or weaken any objective gate.",
      "next_loop_feedback_ref": "judging/synthesis-loop-01/aggregate/synthesis-loop-02-feedback.json",
